{"title_page": "Mazagran (Tourcelles-Chaumont)", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n<!-- See Template:Infobox settlement for additional fields and descriptions -->\n|name                   = Mazagran\n|settlement_type        = Village\n|motto                  =\n|image_skyline          = Plateau de Mazagran.JPG\n|imagesize              = \n|image_caption          = Signboard at village's entrance\n|image_shield           = \n|shield_size            =\n|image_map              = \n|mapsize                = \n|map_caption            = \n|pushpin_map            = France\n|pushpin_label_position = \n|pushpin_map_caption    = Locator map of Mazagran in France\n|pushpin_mapsize        =\n|subdivision_type       = Country\n|subdivision_name       = [[France]]\n|subdivision_type1      = [[Regions of France|Region]]\n|subdivision_name1      = [[Grand Est]]\n|subdivision_type2      = [[Departments of France|Department]]\n|subdivision_name2      = [[Ardennes (department)|Ardennes]]\n|subdivision_type3      = [[Arrondissements of the Ardennes department|Arrondissement]]\n|subdivision_name3      = [[Arrondissement of Vouziers|Vouziers]]\n|subdivision_type4      = [[Cantons of the Ardennes department|Canton]]\n|subdivision_name4      = [[Canton of Machault|Machault]]<ref>{{in lang|fr}} [http://www.annuaire-mairie.fr/canton-machault.html The Canton of Machault on www.annuaire-mairie.fr]</ref>\n|subdivision_type5      = [[Communes of the Ardennes department|Municipality]]\n|subdivision_name5      = [[Tourcelles-Chaumont]]\n|established_date       = \n|area_footnotes         =\n|area_total_km2         =\n|elevation_footnotes    =  \n|elevation_m            = 100\n|population_as_of       = \n|population_footnotes   =\n|population_total       = \n|population_density_km2 = \n|timezone               = [[Central European Time|CET]]\n|utc_offset             = +1\n|timezone_DST           = [[Central European Summer Time|CEST]]\n|utc_offset_DST         = +2\n|coordinates            = {{coord|49|23|35.76|N|4|35|5.8|E|region:FR_type:city|display=inline,title}}\n|postal_code_type       = [[Postal codes in France|Postal code]]\n|postal_code            = 08400\n|area_code              = (+33) ...\n|blank_name             = Demonym\n|blank_info             =\n|website                = <!--{{official|http://www ...}}-->\n|footnotes              = \n}}\n'''Mazagran''' is a [[France|French]] village, part of the municipality (''commune'') of [[Tourcelles-Chaumont]], in the department of [[Ardennes (department)|Ardennes]], [[Grand Est]].\n\n==History==\nThe locality was named after a [[Battle of Mazagran|battle]] holed up in 1840 in the [[Algeria]]n town of [[Mazagran (town)|Mazagran]]; between Algerian resistance forces and French troops, during the [[French conquest of Algeria]].\n\n==Geography==\nSituated in an agricultural [[plateau]] few km from Tourcelles-Chaumont and [[Leffincourt]]; it has a central [[roundabout]] that is a junction point of several national roads to [[Reims]], [[Vouziers]], [[Ch\u00e2lons-en-Champagne]], [[Rethel]] and [[Charleville-M\u00e9zi\u00e8res]]. The proper village is composed by few and scattered farms.\n\n==Literature==\nThe French writer [[Andr\u00e9 Dh\u00f4tel]] set his 1947 novel \"''[[Le Plateau de Mazagran]]''\" in the village.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Villages in Grand Est]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n<!-- See Template:Infobox settlement for additional fields and descriptions -->\n|name                   = Mazagran\n|settlement_type        = Village\n|motto                  =\n|image_skyline          = Plateau de Mazagran.JPG\n|imagesize              = \n|image_caption          = Signboard at village's entrance\n|image_shield           = \n|shield_size            =\n|image_map              = \n|mapsize                = \n|map_caption            = \n|pushpin_map            = France\n|pushpin_label_position = \n|pushpin_map_caption    = Locator map of Mazagran in France\n|pushpin_mapsize        =\n|subdivision_type       = Country\n|subdivision_name       = [[France]]\n|subdivision_type1      = [[Regions of France|Region]]\n|subdivision_name1      = [[Grand Est]]\n|subdivision_type2      = [[Departments of France|Department]]\n|subdivision_name2      = [[Ardennes (department)|Ardennes]]\n|subdivision_type3      = [[Arrondissements of the Ardennes department|Arrondissement]]\n|subdivision_name3      = [[Arrondissement of Vouziers|Vouziers]]\n|subdivision_type4      = [[Cantons of the Ardennes department|Canton]]\n|subdivision_name4      = [[Canton of Machault|Machault]]<ref>{{in lang|fr}} [http://www.annuaire-mairie.fr/canton-machault.html The Canton of Machault on www.annuaire-mairie.fr]</ref>\n|subdivision_type5      = [[Communes of the Ardennes department|Municipality]]\n|subdivision_name5      = [[Tourcelles-Chaumont]]\n|established_date       = \n|area_footnotes         =\n|area_total_km2         =\n|elevation_footnotes    =  \n|elevation_m            = 100\n|population_as_of       = \n|population_footnotes   =\n|population_total       = \n|population_density_km2 = \n|timezone               = [[Central European Time|CET]]\n|utc_offset             = +1\n|timezone_DST           = [[Central European Summer Time|CEST]]\n|utc_offset_DST         = +2\n|coordinates            = {{coord|49|23|35.76|N|4|35|5.8|E|region:FR_type:city|display=inline,title}}\n|postal_code_type       = [[Postal codes in France|Postal code]]\n|postal_code            = 08400\n|area_code              = (+33) ...\n|blank_name             = Demonym\n|blank_info             =\n|website                = <!--{{official|http://www ...}}-->\n|footnotes              = \n}}\n'''Mazagran''' is a [[France|French]] village, part of the municipality (''commune'') of [[Tourcelles-Chaumont]], in the department of [[Ardennes (department)|Ardennes]], [[Grand Est]]. \n\n==History==\nThe locality was named after a [[Battle of Mazagran|battle]] holed up in 1840 in the [[Algeria]]n town of [[Mazagran (town)|Mazagran]]; between Algerian resistance forces and French troops, during the [[French conquest of Algeria]].\n\n==Geography==\nSituated in an agricultural [[plateau]] few km from Tourcelles-Chaumont and [[Leffincourt]]; it has a central [[roundabout]] that is a junction point of several national roads to [[Reims]], [[Vouziers]], [[Ch\u00e2lons-en-Champagne]], [[Rethel]] and [[Charleville-M\u00e9zi\u00e8res]]. The proper village is composed by few and scattered farms.\n\n==Literature==\nThe French writer [[Andr\u00e9 Dh\u00f4tel]] set his 1947 novel \"''[[Le Plateau de Mazagran]]''\" in the village.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Villages in Grand Est]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mazagran_(Tourcelles-Chaumont)"}
